<section class="section">
    <h2>3. Customer Group Management</h2>
    <article class="article">
        <h3>3.1 General Function</h3>
        <p>
            The <strong>Customer Groups</strong> feature allows classifying customers into logical categories to facilitate their management. This enables applying different commercial policies, sending targeted offers, or filtering reports more quickly.
        </p>
    </article>
    <article class="article">
        <h3>3.2 Interface</h3>
        <p>This section presents a simple table with:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>An interactive table listing the registered customer groups, composed of the following fields:
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Customer Group Name</strong>: The name given to a specific group of customers who share common characteristics, purchasing behaviors, or commercial conditions.</li>
                    <li><strong>Percentage Calculation (%)</strong>: Used to apply <strong>discounts, margins, or commissions</strong> based on customer groups or commercial policies.</li>
                    <li><strong>Price Group</strong>: A pricing category that can be associated with one or more customers based on their group.</li>
                    <li><strong>Edit or Delete Actions</strong>: Functions accessible via the "Actions" button to modify or delete the information of a customer or customer group.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>Quick <strong>Action Buttons</strong>:
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Export CSV / Excel / PDF</strong>: allows generating reports on users in the desired format.</li>
                    <li><strong>Direct Printing</strong>: a print button is available to produce a paper version of the list.</li>
                    <li><strong>Column Visibility</strong>: allows hiding or displaying certain columns according to preferences.</li>
                    <li><strong>Dynamic Search</strong>: a quick search field facilitates locating a specific user.</li>
                    <li><strong>Pagination & Number of Entries Per Page</strong>: the user can navigate between pages and choose how many records to display per page (e.g., 10, 25, 50, etc.).</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>
