        <h3>3.4 Using Groups</h3>
        <p>Groups can then be used:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>To <strong>filter customers in views</strong></li>
            <li>To apply specific pricing conditions</li>
            <li>To <strong>segment the customer base during communication campaigns or statistical analysis</strong></li>
        </ul>
    </article>
</section>
<section class="section">
    <h2>4. Importing Contacts</h2>
    <article class="article">
        <h3>4.1 Purpose of the Feature</h3>
        <p>
            The contact import feature allows for the bulk insertion of customer or supplier data from an external file, typically a CSV or Excel file. This is particularly useful during data migration or initial integration.
        </p>
    </article>
    <article class="article">
        <h3>4.2 Interface</h3>
        <p>It presents a simple interface with:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>An "Import" button</li>
            <li>A file upload form</li>
            <li>A preview interface for the data to be imported</li>
            <li>Validation actions</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="image-placeholder">
                <p>Interface Illustration</p>
                <img src="/image/contact6.png" alt="Description de l'image" width="900" height="600" style="max-width:100%;height:auto;border-radius:8px;" />
            </div>
    </article>
    <article class="article">
        <h3>4.3 Import Process</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>Download the modeled file</li>
            <li><strong>Fill in the file</strong></li>
            <li><strong>Select the file to import</strong></li>
            <li><strong>Validate the import by clicking the send button</strong></li>
            <li>The contacts are inserted into the database and automatically classified according to the available columns.</li>
        </ol>
    </article>
    <article class="article">
        <h3>4.4 Benefits</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Significant time savings</strong></li>
            <li><strong>Reduction of manual errors</strong></li>
            <li><strong>Mass update in one click</strong></li>
        </ul>
    </article>
</section>
